### next/font

Next.js's `next/font` module automatically optimizes fonts by self-hosting them. This eliminates external network requests and reduces layout shift.

### Google Fonts

```jsx
import { Inter, Roboto_Mono } from 'next/font/google';

const inter = Inter({
  subsets: ['latin'],
  display: 'swap',
});

const robotoMono = Roboto_Mono({
  subsets: ['latin'],
  display: 'swap',
});

export default function Layout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en" className={inter.className}>
      <body>
        <h1 className={robotoMono.className}>Monospace Heading</h1>
        {children}
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

### Local Fonts

Use local font files with `next/font/local`:

```jsx
import localFont from 'next/font/local';

const myFont = localFont({
  src: './fonts/my-font.woff2',
  display: 'swap',
});

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <div className={myFont.className}>
      <h1>Custom Local Font</h1>
    </div>
  );
}
```

You can also specify multiple src files for different formats or weights:

```jsx
const myFont = localFont({
  src: [
    { path: './fonts/MyFont-Regular.woff2', weight: '400' },
    { path: './fonts/MyFont-Bold.woff2', weight: '700' },
  ],
});
```

### Variable Fonts

Google variable fonts are supported out of the box:

```jsx
const inter = Inter({
  subsets: ['latin'],
  variable: '--font-inter',
});

// Use CSS variable
<html className={inter.variable}>
<body style={{ fontFamily: 'var(--font-inter)' }}>
```

### Performance Benefits

- **Zero layout shift**: Fonts are loaded before rendering
- **No external requests**: Self-hosted, no Google server round-trip
- **Smaller payloads**: Subset loading (e.g., only latin characters)
- **Automatic optimization**: Font files are optimized and hashed

codeExample:
import { Inter } from 'next/font/google';

const inter = Inter({
  subsets: ['latin'],
  weight: ['400', '700'],
});

export default function Home() {
  return (
    <div className={inter.className}>
      <h1>Optimized Font</h1>
      <p>This text uses Inter font, self-hosted by Next.js.</p>
    </div>
  );
}
